WEBVTT

00:03.003 --> 00:05.005
[grand orchestral fanfare
playing]

00:41.911 --> 00:43.608
♪ ♪

00:55.403 --> 00:57.840
♪ ♪

01:11.419 --> 01:14.117
♪ ♪

01:16.467 --> 01:18.686
Supermoon events occur
when the full moon

01:18.687 --> 01:20.340
is at its closest orbit
to the Earth,

01:20.341 --> 01:23.517
roughly 223,000 miles away.

01:23.518 --> 01:26.825
This can happen
multiple times a year, but...

01:27.870 --> 01:30.828
...last year was different.

01:30.829 --> 01:33.962
FEMALE REPORTER: <i>I'm speaking
with Dr. James Aranda.</i>

01:33.963 --> 01:37.400
<i>So tell me, Doctor, why hasn't
this happened before?</i>

01:37.401 --> 01:39.576
Why now?
Is it genetically modified food

01:39.577 --> 01:42.450
- or a weaponized virus?
- All right, let's just, uh...

01:43.799 --> 01:46.148
Let's focus on what we do know.
[sighs]

01:46.149 --> 01:49.891
No one, and I mean no one

01:49.892 --> 01:52.460
should be exposed to moonlight
tonight. That's number one.

01:54.331 --> 01:55.898
Number two is fear.

01:56.986 --> 01:59.206
Fear makes bad decisions.

02:00.685 --> 02:02.425
Have a plan,

02:02.426 --> 02:03.731
stick to it,

02:03.732 --> 02:05.212
and stay safe.

02:06.256 --> 02:08.214
Number three, number three...

02:08.215 --> 02:10.172
Everyone should know
that we are working

02:10.173 --> 02:12.784
around the clock
to find a solution.

02:14.090 --> 02:16.265
We will survive this.

02:16.266 --> 02:18.312
♪ ♪

02:35.633 --> 02:37.678
We got you your favorite, Sean.

02:37.679 --> 02:39.507
Chocolate cupcake.

02:41.770 --> 02:44.511
We know you loved these
on your birthday.

02:44.512 --> 02:46.166
I wish you were here with us.

02:48.603 --> 02:50.039
I miss you.

02:51.823 --> 02:53.085
We love you, Dad.

02:56.045 --> 02:57.045
[blows]

02:57.046 --> 02:59.135
♪ ♪

03:09.145 --> 03:11.452
[indistinct shouting
in distance]

03:23.072 --> 03:24.421
[kid shouting]

03:29.078 --> 03:31.167
[indistinct shouting continues]

03:39.871 --> 03:41.960
♪ ♪

03:46.356 --> 03:47.530
MAN:
Come on, let's go!

03:47.531 --> 03:49.229
[chatter continues indistinctly]

04:13.862 --> 04:15.907
♪ ♪

04:17.169 --> 04:18.606
[indistinct chatter in distance]

04:23.611 --> 04:25.656
MAN:
No time. Keep moving.

04:27.876 --> 04:32.010
[gunfire]

04:43.413 --> 04:47.677
ARANDA [on video]: My team and I
have spent our entire careers,

04:47.678 --> 04:50.072
fighting against some
of nature's worst creations.

04:51.508 --> 04:53.509
Found a way before,

04:53.510 --> 04:55.295
and we will again.

04:58.036 --> 04:59.733
It's important to remember
that this is not just

04:59.734 --> 05:01.518
a global effort.

05:02.824 --> 05:04.433
This is a human effort.

05:04.434 --> 05:08.481
A way of life,
what we stand for,

05:08.482 --> 05:10.701
the people that we love.

05:12.747 --> 05:15.183
This is what
we're fighting for tonight.

05:15.184 --> 05:17.664
- [doorbell rings]
- [knock on door]

05:17.665 --> 05:19.492
Hey.

05:19.493 --> 05:21.407
My mom thought
these might cheer Emma up.

05:21.408 --> 05:23.452
Tell her I said thank you.
I have something for you.

05:23.453 --> 05:24.759
Emma.

05:26.543 --> 05:28.762
- Hey, kiddo.
- Hi, Reagan.

05:28.763 --> 05:30.503
MAN [on TV]:
When the curfew starts,

05:30.504 --> 05:33.462
please don't go outside.
Please find shelter...

05:33.463 --> 05:35.508
Spare batteries,
in case the power goes out.

05:35.509 --> 05:38.075
Make sure your phone is charged.

05:38.076 --> 05:39.729
Pepper spray.

05:39.730 --> 05:41.210
Just in case.

05:42.733 --> 05:44.996
Thank you so much,
Mrs. Marshall.

05:45.997 --> 05:47.041
Come on.

05:47.042 --> 05:49.392
- [gunfire]
- [grunts]

05:51.351 --> 05:55.919
Cody! Cody!

05:55.920 --> 05:57.573
[panting]

05:57.574 --> 05:59.053
Wesley.

05:59.054 --> 06:01.055
What are you doing, man?
You're shooting your gun

06:01.056 --> 06:03.536
right at Lucy's house.
My niece is inside.

06:03.537 --> 06:05.799
There's kids all over the place.
You can kill somebody.

06:05.800 --> 06:08.497
I'm just trying to get ready
for tonight, Captain.

06:08.498 --> 06:10.586
I'm not in the military
anymore, Cody.

06:10.587 --> 06:12.936
We are all soldiers now.

06:12.937 --> 06:15.852
You see what's happening
in Tokyo right now? Or Sydney?

06:15.853 --> 06:18.594
Hell's coming our way, Wesley.

06:18.595 --> 06:20.901
- Hell.
- Is that right?

06:20.902 --> 06:23.120
You know,
I don't understand you, sir.

06:23.121 --> 06:24.731
You're here to protect
your brother's family,

06:24.732 --> 06:26.123
and this is how you do it,

06:26.124 --> 06:27.734
with plywood
and chain-link fencing?

06:27.735 --> 06:29.344
You don't worry
about my brother's family.

06:29.345 --> 06:30.476
I got it covered.

06:30.477 --> 06:32.347
I pray to God you do.

06:32.348 --> 06:35.394
Because tonight,
when that sun sets,

06:35.395 --> 06:37.484
it's gonna be
every man for himself.

06:39.486 --> 06:41.269
Good luck tonight, Cody.

06:41.270 --> 06:43.228
I don't need luck.

06:51.019 --> 06:54.978
SEAN [on tape]: Hey, Lucy bear.
Repeat after me, okay?

06:54.979 --> 06:57.938
- My home is a sacred ground.
- My home is a sacred ground.

06:57.939 --> 06:59.418
BOTH:
I will protect myself

06:59.419 --> 07:02.508
and the ones I love
at all costs.

07:02.509 --> 07:05.032
- SEAN: I am a survivor.
- LUCY: I'm a survivor.

07:05.033 --> 07:07.687
SEAN:
I am strong. I am capable...

07:07.688 --> 07:09.123
All right.
I double and triple-checked

07:09.124 --> 07:11.605
all the windows and locks.

07:12.867 --> 07:14.215
The house is good.

07:14.216 --> 07:16.087
What?

07:17.349 --> 07:19.350
The house, it's all locked up.

07:19.351 --> 07:20.917
All right,
just like we practiced

07:20.918 --> 07:22.223
at the range a thousand times.

07:22.224 --> 07:24.617
You chamber the round,
you aim...

07:24.618 --> 07:26.270
and fire.

07:26.271 --> 07:29.100
- Okay. -You're not gonna
have to use this.

07:30.101 --> 07:31.363
Let's go over the rules.

07:32.495 --> 07:34.191
Wes, I remember the rules.

07:34.192 --> 07:36.238
Are you sure?

07:37.457 --> 07:39.153
- Don't open the door for anyone.
- Yeah.

07:39.154 --> 07:41.198
Don't make any noise.
Don't draw attention.

07:41.199 --> 07:45.420
Don't hesitate for a second.
I don't care who it is.

07:45.421 --> 07:47.422
- Okay?
- Okay.

07:47.423 --> 07:49.468
All right. You call me
if there's an emergency.

07:49.469 --> 07:51.818
If not, I'll...
I'll reach out to you.

07:51.819 --> 07:54.169
We got this.

07:55.475 --> 07:56.910
- Good.
- We're good. We're good.

07:56.911 --> 07:58.172
We're good. Okay.

07:58.173 --> 07:59.914
[knocking on door]

08:03.265 --> 08:04.745
What's wrong, kiddo?

08:06.094 --> 08:08.095
- Uncle Wes?
- Yeah.

08:08.096 --> 08:09.749
Why can't you stay?

08:09.750 --> 08:11.533
I want to stay.

08:11.534 --> 08:13.187
I want to stay
more than anything,

08:13.188 --> 08:17.017
but they need me to help them
try and stop this.

08:17.018 --> 08:19.281
I don't want to die.

08:20.717 --> 08:23.241
Hey. [sighs] Look at me.

08:25.156 --> 08:27.157
You're not gonna die.

08:27.158 --> 08:31.988
Nothing is going
to happen to you, okay?

08:31.989 --> 08:34.556
Do you remember when Daddy
used to tell you that story

08:34.557 --> 08:37.254
about the three little pigs
and the big bad wolf?

08:37.255 --> 08:39.256
- Mm-hmm.
- Yeah?

08:39.257 --> 08:41.432
Do you remember why the big bad
wolf couldn't get in the house?

08:41.433 --> 08:43.217
Because it was made of bricks?

08:43.218 --> 08:47.918
It was made of bricks,
just like your house.

08:49.311 --> 08:52.575
Nothing is going to get in.
I made sure of it.

08:54.664 --> 08:56.187
I promise.

09:21.561 --> 09:22.736
LUCY:
It's getting late.

09:24.999 --> 09:26.566
You should get going.

09:29.307 --> 09:30.960
I don't think I can do this.

09:30.961 --> 09:32.572
Wesley...

09:35.618 --> 09:37.359
We're the only family
we have left.

09:38.969 --> 09:41.275
They'll figure it out.
They'll understand.

09:41.276 --> 09:43.974
They can't do this without you.

09:45.889 --> 09:47.673
And Sean...

09:47.674 --> 09:49.937
he would want you to go.

09:54.594 --> 09:56.291
"Always ready."

10:24.885 --> 10:27.627
[indistinct chatter in distance]

10:51.563 --> 10:53.609
[helicopter blades whirring]

10:57.482 --> 10:59.396
[seagulls squawking]

10:59.397 --> 11:01.137
Let's go! Let's go! Come on!

11:01.138 --> 11:04.010
Let's go! Let's go!
Move it! Drive on. This way.

11:04.011 --> 11:06.665
MAN [on P.A.]: Transportation
to the underground is limited.

11:06.666 --> 11:09.406
Bring only what you need
to survive the night.

11:09.407 --> 11:12.409
Thank you for your cooperation.

11:12.410 --> 11:14.760
[indistinct chatter]

11:14.761 --> 11:16.500
MAN [on P.A.]: Curfew is
in place for your protection.

11:16.501 --> 11:18.460
Please return
to your homes immediately.

11:20.331 --> 11:22.203
SOLDIER:
One second, sir.

11:24.335 --> 11:27.163
MAN [on P.A.]: Transportation
to the underground is limited.

11:27.164 --> 11:28.991
Bring only what you need
to survive the night.

11:28.992 --> 11:30.951
SOLDIER: All right.
Go ahead, Dr. Marshall.

11:31.952 --> 11:34.344
Thank you.

11:34.345 --> 11:37.218
MAN [on P.A.]: Curfew is
in place for your protection.

11:56.237 --> 11:57.717
Yeah, okay.

12:01.764 --> 12:02.896
[grunts]

12:07.161 --> 12:08.728
[muttering]

12:34.362 --> 12:35.841
MAN [on radio]: They don't
care about our rights.

12:35.842 --> 12:36.972
WOMAN [on radio]:
That's right. Our right

12:36.973 --> 12:38.669
is to kill these motherfuckers.

12:38.670 --> 12:39.758
MAN [on radio]: Yeah, yeah.
It's up to us tonight

12:39.759 --> 12:41.194
to fight these things.

12:41.195 --> 12:43.370
It's up to us
to keep America safe.

12:43.371 --> 12:44.588
WOMAN [on radio]:
We are supposed to keep

12:44.589 --> 12:46.547
our people safe.

12:46.548 --> 12:48.114
MAN [on radio]: That's right.
They're not gonna do it for us.

12:48.115 --> 12:50.943
We have to do it for ourselves.

12:50.944 --> 12:54.381
ARANDA: <i>I trust that everyone
made plans for your loved ones.</i>

12:54.382 --> 12:57.079
I know it's not easy.

12:57.080 --> 12:59.603
We have a nine-hour window

12:59.604 --> 13:03.738
to assess, test,
and report our findings.

13:03.739 --> 13:07.176
I would like to introduce
Wesley Marshall,

13:07.177 --> 13:09.439
Global Rapid Response
team leader

13:09.440 --> 13:11.051
and lead molecular biologist.

13:12.487 --> 13:14.227
Evan Radcliffe
is second in command.

13:14.228 --> 13:16.055
And Amy Chen,

13:16.056 --> 13:20.711
chief <i>Canis lupus</i> biologist
and behavioralist.

13:20.712 --> 13:23.454
They have been spearheading
our work here tonight.

13:26.066 --> 13:27.109
[TV clicks on]

13:27.110 --> 13:29.459
Now we know that the supermoon

13:29.460 --> 13:31.200
triggers rapid DNA mutation,

13:31.201 --> 13:33.115
and is photosensitive
to moonlight.

13:33.116 --> 13:37.163
We hope to see
if this mutation can be blocked.

13:37.164 --> 13:39.643
This team standing behind me
has developed a liquid

13:39.644 --> 13:43.169
we call "Moonscreen."

13:43.170 --> 13:44.866
It is our hope

13:44.867 --> 13:47.521
that this Moonscreen
acts as a barrier

13:47.522 --> 13:50.177
between the moonlight
and human DNA.

13:53.528 --> 13:58.662
What we discover tonight could
go a long way to finding a cure.

13:58.663 --> 14:01.230
It is not hyperbole to say

14:01.231 --> 14:05.888
that our discoveries
could save millions of lives.

14:08.586 --> 14:11.675
Emergency services
will be suspended

14:11.676 --> 14:14.243
from sunset to sunrise.

14:14.244 --> 14:17.595
Please stay out
of the moonlight.

14:20.598 --> 14:21.861
Good luck tonight.

14:23.906 --> 14:29.432
[yelling]

14:29.433 --> 14:31.434
WOMAN [on P.A.]: Please
be advised, for your safety,

14:31.435 --> 14:33.436
we are now in full lockdown.

14:33.437 --> 14:35.177
No one will be permitted
to enter

14:35.178 --> 14:37.310
or leave the facility
until daybreak.

14:37.311 --> 14:40.140
All exit points
have been sealed.

14:54.763 --> 14:56.460
[indistinct chatter]

15:08.037 --> 15:10.344
AUTOMATED VOICE: Subject
number three entering facility.

15:13.390 --> 15:15.740
Subject number three
entering facility.

15:22.573 --> 15:24.053
MYLES: <i>Amy...</i>

15:26.838 --> 15:30.930
Whatever happens tonight,
remember, it is my choice.

15:33.280 --> 15:34.411
I know.

15:37.849 --> 15:39.721
I love you, Dr. Chen.

16:05.529 --> 16:07.704
Don't worry, Dr. Chen.

16:07.705 --> 16:09.968
We've taken
every safety precaution.

16:09.969 --> 16:12.058
He's gonna be okay.

16:23.765 --> 16:25.896
Myles can feel the supermoon
is about to rise.

16:25.897 --> 16:28.639
All the Year Oners
know it's close.

16:29.858 --> 16:31.425
They can feel it.

16:33.427 --> 16:37.647
Whatever turned him last year
left a compulsive craving.

16:37.648 --> 16:39.999
He's an addict without a fix.

16:41.870 --> 16:44.219
Until tonight.

16:44.220 --> 16:46.005
[door buzzes]

16:52.968 --> 16:54.229
MAN [on radio]:
We are now entering

16:54.230 --> 16:55.926
the final hour of daylight.

16:55.927 --> 16:59.017
Our prayers are with everyone,

16:59.018 --> 17:00.888
and the team at Aranda Corp.

17:00.889 --> 17:03.064
Let us hope they find us a cure.

17:03.065 --> 17:07.416
Stay safe out there, everyone,
and Godspeed.

17:07.417 --> 17:10.593
[video game beeping]

17:10.594 --> 17:13.901
Scoot over, kiddo.
Mama needs in on this game.

17:13.902 --> 17:16.164
You know
I always beat you, right?

17:16.165 --> 17:18.732
Oh, it's like, it's like that?
Is it like that?

17:18.733 --> 17:20.647
- [both laugh]
- Is it really like that?

17:20.648 --> 17:23.171
But who wins the tickling?

17:23.172 --> 17:26.871
Who-who-who? Who wins at
tickling, Emma? Tell me.

17:29.874 --> 17:33.007
AUTOMATED VOICE:
30 minutes to canopy retraction.

17:33.008 --> 17:35.141
30 minutes to canopy retraction.

17:36.272 --> 17:38.361
30 minutes to canopy retraction.

17:43.627 --> 17:46.674
Hey. You okay?

17:49.155 --> 17:51.330
We're in it together. Yeah?

17:51.331 --> 17:55.596
Breathe. Just breathe.

18:01.254 --> 18:03.952
Three, two, one...

18:07.564 --> 18:09.565
[buzzing]

18:09.566 --> 18:10.785
Go time.

18:12.352 --> 18:14.615
[door hisses]

18:19.446 --> 18:21.273
ARANDA:
All staff to stations.

18:21.274 --> 18:23.753
MALE SCIENTIST: Hey, Phil,
we're over here on Subject One.

18:23.754 --> 18:26.366
PHIL:
Copy. Moving in.

18:28.846 --> 18:31.066
Sir. Step forward.

18:33.329 --> 18:34.896
FEMALE SCIENTIST:
Good luck tonight, sir.

18:36.724 --> 18:38.333
MALE SCIENTIST:
Whoa, whoa, ma'am, ma'am.

18:38.334 --> 18:41.423
- [woman whimpering]
- Ma'am, I need you to stay calm.

18:41.424 --> 18:43.251
Your heart rate
is incredibly elevated.

18:43.252 --> 18:44.992
Good.

18:44.993 --> 18:47.212
MALE SCIENTIST:
Hey, hey, you sure this guy

18:47.213 --> 18:49.127
passed the psych eval?

18:49.128 --> 18:51.825
FEMALE SCIENTIST: It's not like
we had a lot of volunteers.

18:51.826 --> 18:53.696
EVAN: [sighs] How come
I always get the crazy ones?

18:53.697 --> 18:56.046
FEMALE SCIENTIST:
Right?

18:56.047 --> 18:59.093
MALE SCIENTIST: Moonscreen
temperature... stable.

18:59.094 --> 19:00.964
I really don't like
the name "Moonscreen."

19:00.965 --> 19:03.664
We commence in ten minutes.
Ten-minute warning.

19:06.275 --> 19:07.928
AUTOMATED VOICE:
Ten-minute warning.

19:07.929 --> 19:09.799
Ten-minute warning.

19:09.800 --> 19:11.627
I can't believe
they volunteered for this.

19:11.628 --> 19:13.673
- Let me get in there.
- Go ahead.

19:13.674 --> 19:15.370
SCIENTIST:
Excuse me, sir.

19:15.371 --> 19:16.632
EVAN: You don't even know
if the Moonscreen will work.

19:16.633 --> 19:19.548
It'll work. It has to work.

19:19.549 --> 19:22.421
PHIL: Subject Three,
step forward, please.

19:22.422 --> 19:24.336
Don't worry,
it's just a liquid nanotech

19:24.337 --> 19:25.554
to protect your eyes.

19:25.555 --> 19:26.687
It won't hurt.

19:31.170 --> 19:33.736
WESLEY: All right.
Liquid lens team out.

19:33.737 --> 19:36.783
- Formula team in.
- MALE SCIENTIST: Vitals out.

19:36.784 --> 19:39.568
God, I hope this works.
Good luck tonight, guys.

19:39.569 --> 19:40.875
WESLEY:
Keep moving.

19:41.702 --> 19:43.398
SCIENTIST:
Good luck.

19:43.399 --> 19:45.313
AUTOMATED VOICE: Five minutes
to canopy retraction.

19:45.314 --> 19:47.185
- [chuckling]
- Five minutes

19:47.186 --> 19:49.013
to canopy retraction.

19:52.713 --> 19:55.368
WESLEY: Spray him down.
Make sure you get all of it.

19:57.979 --> 19:59.328
Start the clock.

20:00.547 --> 20:02.157
Notate how long
the screen lasts.

20:03.202 --> 20:04.898
WESLEY:
Starting the clock.

20:04.899 --> 20:06.291
SCIENTIST 1:
All right, spray down.

20:06.292 --> 20:07.727
SCIENTIST 2:
Security, be ready.

20:07.728 --> 20:08.989
Screen them up, guys.
Screen them up.

20:08.990 --> 20:10.034
SCIENTIST 3:
Good over here.

20:15.214 --> 20:16.954
PHIL:
Chin up, chin up.

20:18.347 --> 20:21.306
[cackles]

20:21.307 --> 20:24.265
AUTOMATED VOICE: Three minutes
to canopy retraction.

20:24.266 --> 20:26.528
Three minutes
to canopy retraction.

20:26.529 --> 20:28.965
Three minutes to
canopy retraction.

20:28.966 --> 20:31.446
What happens if one of them
decides to moon the sky

20:31.447 --> 20:33.753
once we open up this roof?

20:33.754 --> 20:36.625
The formula penetrates
the thin fibers, Evan.

20:36.626 --> 20:38.889
No one's showing their ass
and turning tonight.

20:40.456 --> 20:43.110
[woman whimpering]

20:43.111 --> 20:45.635
I changed my mind.

20:48.377 --> 20:50.422
Hey. Hey.

20:50.423 --> 20:51.988
Hey. Are you listening to me?

20:51.989 --> 20:53.642
SCIENTIST:
We're losing Subject One.

20:53.643 --> 20:55.992
AUTOMATED VOICE: Two minutes
to canopy retraction.

20:55.993 --> 20:57.342
WOMAN:
Help me!

20:57.343 --> 20:59.344
Two minutes
to canopy retraction.

20:59.345 --> 21:00.693
[grunts]

21:00.694 --> 21:02.956
Wait, wait, where are you going?

21:02.957 --> 21:05.480
[cries]
Please, let me out of here!

21:05.481 --> 21:07.266
- AMY: Should we sedate her?
- No.

21:08.528 --> 21:11.226
Sedatives could interfere
with the test results.

21:13.184 --> 21:15.708
She knew what
she was getting into.

21:15.709 --> 21:17.927
[crying]:
I don't want to turn. No.

21:17.928 --> 21:19.233
[screams]

21:19.234 --> 21:21.714
SUBJECT 2:
Please open this gate!

21:21.715 --> 21:23.803
Hey! It's gonna be okay.

21:23.804 --> 21:25.021
No.

21:25.022 --> 21:26.588
[screams]

21:26.589 --> 21:30.157
- Just relax. It's gonna work.
- Hey!

21:30.158 --> 21:32.115
- [laughing]
- [yells]

