Yeah!

22:28.782 --> 22:30.784
♪ ♪

22:46.321 --> 22:48.235
[yells]

22:48.236 --> 22:50.499
What's happening?!

22:52.066 --> 22:54.372
He's fine. It fucking worked.

22:54.373 --> 22:56.286
EVAN:
I think we're through.

22:56.287 --> 22:58.159
SCIENTIST 1:
I think we did it.

23:07.429 --> 23:10.519
SCIENTIST 2: Dr. Aranda,
I think it's holding.

23:13.783 --> 23:15.741
Start pulling fluid
and tissue biopsies.

23:15.742 --> 23:17.525
Let's get everything
analyzed ASAP.

23:17.526 --> 23:19.527
Subjects Two
and Three are Year Oners.

23:19.528 --> 23:21.050
I want a comparison test

23:21.051 --> 23:23.009
to see if they exhibit
any abnormalities

23:23.010 --> 23:25.054
relative to our test group.

23:25.055 --> 23:26.882
Dr. Chen,

23:26.883 --> 23:28.928
I need you to analyze
those blood samples

23:28.929 --> 23:30.886
from our <i>Canis lupus.</i>

23:30.887 --> 23:32.585
Yes, sir.

23:36.980 --> 23:38.547
[insects trilling]

23:41.158 --> 23:42.202
[snarling]

23:42.203 --> 23:45.772
[distant howling]

23:49.036 --> 23:51.430
[howling continues]

23:55.956 --> 23:57.347
Hey, I'll be right outside.

23:57.348 --> 23:59.219
I just wanna go
check on things, okay?

23:59.220 --> 24:01.570
