[creaking]

24:45.788 --> 24:47.224
Mom?

24:49.052 --> 24:50.270
[distant thudding]

24:50.271 --> 24:51.533
[creaking]

25:15.209 --> 25:17.472
[door creaking]

25:18.647 --> 25:19.778
[Reagan exhales]

25:19.779 --> 25:23.346
[low growl]

25:23.347 --> 25:26.612
- [growling grows louder]
- [breathing heavily]

25:34.097 --> 25:35.229
[snarls]

25:36.360 --> 25:38.275
[beeping]

25:42.105 --> 25:43.541
[buzzer buzzing]

25:43.542 --> 25:44.804
Stepping in now.

25:47.328 --> 25:48.328
SCIENTIST 1:
Congratulations, Doctor.

25:48.329 --> 25:50.243
FEMALE SCIENTIST:
Stable.

25:50.244 --> 25:51.984
SCIENTIST 2:
Blood's looking good.

25:51.985 --> 25:53.812
- Let's relay positive results.
- Very nice. Looks good.

25:53.813 --> 25:57.424
SCIENTIST 3: Mitosis seems
to be holding, no mutations.

25:57.425 --> 25:59.470
ARANDA: How are the samples
looking, Wes?

26:02.473 --> 26:03.997
You seeing this?

26:10.351 --> 26:11.656
Is it parasitic?

26:11.657 --> 26:13.135
WESLEY: I don't know.
It looks like it

26:13.136 --> 26:15.747
might be kind of
an immunological defense system.

26:15.748 --> 26:17.400
Whatever this mutation is,

26:17.401 --> 26:18.837
it looks like the supermoon's

26:18.838 --> 26:21.317
triggering
a dormant defense response.

26:21.318 --> 26:23.232
ARANDA:
But why is it only now reactive?

26:23.233 --> 26:25.800
Could it be viral
or pathological?

26:25.801 --> 26:27.628
I don't know yet.

26:27.629 --> 26:31.241
Evan, bring me
a different tissue sample.

26:32.460 --> 26:33.722
[grunts]

26:36.420 --> 26:38.334
Subject Three is turning.

26:38.335 --> 26:39.640
Moonscreen stability
at one hour.

26:39.641 --> 26:41.947
[yelling]

26:41.948 --> 26:43.602
PHIL: Stay back.
Everybody, stay back.

26:46.430 --> 26:48.345
[cackling]

26:50.043 --> 26:51.566
[yells]

26:52.959 --> 26:54.437
Fuck.

26:54.438 --> 26:56.092
WESLEY:
Get that formula spraying now.

26:58.486 --> 27:00.182
Yes!

27:00.183 --> 27:02.055
ARANDA: Where the fuck
is the Moonscreen?

27:06.581 --> 27:07.886
SCIENTIST:
Oh, fuck!

27:07.887 --> 27:09.322
SOLDIER:
Dr. Aranda, what's the status?

27:09.323 --> 27:10.192
- Look out! Look out!
- Move back!

27:10.193 --> 27:11.411
Get back now!

27:11.412 --> 27:12.978
[growling]

27:12.979 --> 27:14.415
SCIENTIST:
Dr. Aranda!

27:16.504 --> 27:18.766
Spray the formula, now.

27:18.767 --> 27:19.986
[breathing heavily]
Yeah, yeah, all right.

27:22.075 --> 27:23.292
[grunts]

27:23.293 --> 27:25.381
[groans]

27:25.382 --> 27:27.122
[yells]

27:27.123 --> 27:28.254
[growls]

27:28.255 --> 27:29.343
SCIENTIST:
Watch out!

27:30.692 --> 27:32.433
- [indistinct shouting]
- Move, move!

27:34.478 --> 27:36.523
Oh, shit.

27:36.524 --> 27:39.831
Close the roof!
Close the roof!

27:39.832 --> 27:40.876
MAN: Go!

27:44.880 --> 27:46.185
SCIENTIST:
The roof isn't closing.

27:46.186 --> 27:47.970
AUTOMATED VOICE:
Canopy malfunctioning.

27:48.971 --> 27:51.146
Canopy malfunctioning.

27:51.147 --> 27:53.496
[bones cracking]

27:53.497 --> 27:55.063
[growling]

27:55.064 --> 27:57.065
[yells]

27:57.066 --> 27:59.721
[grunting]

28:00.853 --> 28:03.594
[roars]

28:04.639 --> 28:06.206
[indistinct shouting]

28:07.207 --> 28:08.556
[groans]

28:11.951 --> 28:13.256
Everyone get to an exit.

28:13.953 --> 28:15.344
Now!

28:15.345 --> 28:17.346
WESLEY:
James! James, are you okay?

28:17.347 --> 28:20.350
ARANDA:
My suit... my suit ripped.

28:22.048 --> 28:23.439
WESLEY: You're gonna be okay.
You hear me?

28:23.440 --> 28:25.703
- [breathing heavily]
- [beeping rapidly]

28:25.704 --> 28:27.487
He's been exposed.
He's been exposed.

28:27.488 --> 28:29.141
SOLDIER: Wes, what the fuck
did you just say?

28:29.142 --> 28:30.578
I need a tranquilizer now.

28:31.797 --> 28:32.798
Evan, hurry up.

28:36.540 --> 28:38.673
- ARANDA: Wes, go.
- WESLEY: James, stay with me.

28:39.892 --> 28:41.893
- Fuck, he's turning.
- [Aranda moans]

28:41.894 --> 28:42.895
[growls]

28:43.939 --> 28:45.592
Where is the tranquilizer?

28:45.593 --> 28:48.247
- I'm coming!
- [screaming]

28:48.248 --> 28:50.597
WESLEY: James, stay with me.
James! You can fight this.

28:50.598 --> 28:54.907
ARANDA: [screams]
Get away from me! Get away!

28:55.951 --> 28:57.910
[roars]

29:04.090 --> 29:05.787
WESLEY:
Hit him with the tranquilizer!

29:06.396 --> 29:07.963
[screams]

29:13.142 --> 29:14.143
[roars]

29:18.365 --> 29:21.062
- I can't breathe. [gasps]
- Fuck.

29:21.063 --> 29:22.761
WESLEY:
Go! Let's go, let's go!

29:29.419 --> 29:31.204
[low growl]

29:33.859 --> 29:35.033
Go!

29:35.034 --> 29:37.078
[wheezing]

29:37.079 --> 29:38.732
[beeping rapidly]

29:38.733 --> 29:40.648
I can't breathe.

29:42.171 --> 29:44.738
I'm living.
I can't... I can't breathe.

29:44.739 --> 29:46.958
[alarm sounding]

29:46.959 --> 29:48.655
AUTOMATED VOICE:
Attention. All staff,

29:48.656 --> 29:50.310
please move to emergency exits.

29:52.921 --> 29:54.617
Finish gathering
the blood samples.

29:54.618 --> 29:56.750
Then I want you
moving to an exit.

29:56.751 --> 29:57.838
AUTOMATED VOICE:
Attention. All staff,

29:57.839 --> 29:58.970
please move to emergency exits.

29:58.971 --> 30:00.232
[Evan groans, wheezes]

30:00.233 --> 30:02.060
I got you. You're okay.

30:02.061 --> 30:03.409
AUTOMATED VOICE:
Attention. All staff,

30:03.410 --> 30:05.150
please move to emergency exits.

30:05.151 --> 30:07.630
WESLEY:
It's okay.

30:07.631 --> 30:09.284
AUTOMATED VOICE:
Attention. All staff,

30:09.285 --> 30:10.503
please move to emergency exits.

30:10.504 --> 30:11.852
SOLDIER:
Is everyone okay?

30:11.853 --> 30:14.072
FEMALE SCIENTIST:
I gotta get out of here.

30:14.073 --> 30:15.116
SOLDIER:
Shut up! Shut up! Shut up!

30:15.117 --> 30:16.815
Quiet! Quiet! Quiet.

30:18.817 --> 30:20.992
- Where the fuck are you?
- FEMALE SCIENTIST: I can't...

30:20.993 --> 30:24.952
I can't see anything.
I don't wanna fucking die.

30:24.953 --> 30:27.346
SOLDIER 1: No, okay.
Everyone just stay calm.

30:27.347 --> 30:29.565
We're gonna get out of here.

30:29.566 --> 30:31.917
[growling]

30:34.354 --> 30:35.834
SOLDIER 2: No!

30:37.400 --> 30:38.923
[female scientist screams]

30:38.924 --> 30:40.969
SOLDIER 1: Got you,
you wolf piece of shit!

30:42.492 --> 30:44.103
[screams]

30:47.802 --> 30:49.847
Die, you fucking bastard!

30:49.848 --> 30:51.806
[screaming]

30:56.637 --> 30:57.986
WOMAN:
Just go, just go.

30:59.553 --> 31:02.163
MAN:
Get out! Go, go!

31:02.164 --> 31:03.599
- What's happening?
- RESEARCHER: Sorry.

31:03.600 --> 31:05.601
Keep going.
To your right. Keep going.

31:05.602 --> 31:07.734
- [Evan wheezing]
- [indistinct shouting]

31:07.735 --> 31:09.868
You're okay.
You're gonna be okay.

31:11.130 --> 31:13.741
Stay with me. Come on.

31:14.394 --> 31:15.829
[yelps]

31:15.830 --> 31:17.005
[explosion]

31:21.053 --> 31:23.751
No, no, no! Go! Go, go!

31:26.406 --> 31:28.364
[breathing heavily]

31:32.151 --> 31:33.630
[screams]

31:34.980 --> 31:36.502
Wes.

31:36.503 --> 31:39.679
Oh, my God, Evan! Infirmary.

31:39.680 --> 31:41.072
[low growl]

31:41.073 --> 31:43.291
[loud snarl]

31:43.292 --> 31:44.424
Out of the hall.

31:45.425 --> 31:46.991
- Go!
- [woman screams in distance]

31:46.992 --> 31:49.777
- [buzzing]
- Wes, it's not working.

31:53.868 --> 31:54.868
Wes...

31:54.869 --> 31:58.394
[growls]

32:04.357 --> 32:05.401
WESLEY: Go!

32:06.576 --> 32:08.491
[buzzing]

32:14.671 --> 32:15.715
[beeps]

32:15.716 --> 32:17.892
WESLEY:
Go! Go!

32:21.113 --> 32:22.418
[Amy screams]

32:24.899 --> 32:27.161
SOLDIER:
Shoot it! Shoot it!

32:27.162 --> 32:28.510
[gunfire]

32:28.511 --> 32:30.165
[werewolf groans]

32:33.821 --> 32:36.301
[soldier yells]

32:36.302 --> 32:38.564
[gunfire]

32:38.565 --> 32:40.088
SOLDIER:
Jesus Christ!

32:46.094 --> 32:47.661
[coughing]

32:49.793 --> 32:52.882
[breathing heavily]

32:52.883 --> 32:54.450
[keyboard clacking]

32:56.539 --> 32:59.412
- [howling in distance]
- [grunts]

33:04.852 --> 33:06.506
[growling in distance]

33:13.295 --> 33:15.122
[snarling]

33:15.123 --> 33:16.298
[gasps]

33:17.299 --> 33:19.649
[objects clattering]

33:22.739 --> 33:24.306
[growling]

33:28.963 --> 33:31.879
[Cody breathing heavily]

33:39.974 --> 33:40.974
[Cody yells]

33:40.975 --> 33:42.672
[gasps]

33:47.851 --> 33:49.114
[gunfire continues]

34:00.603 --> 34:03.736
WESLEY:
All right. You're all right.

34:03.737 --> 34:04.867
AMY:
We have to stop the bleeding.

34:04.868 --> 34:06.826
Move, move, move, move, move!

34:06.827 --> 34:08.393
- WESLEY: Okay.
- Okay, hold it down. Pressure!

34:08.394 --> 34:10.917
Pressure. Evan?
Evan, stick with us, okay?

34:10.918 --> 34:13.093
You just breathe slowly. We're
gonna get you patched up, okay?

34:13.094 --> 34:14.834
- WESLEY: Breathe, Evan, breathe.
- Hold both hands. Both...

34:14.835 --> 34:16.575
- WESLEY: I got it. I got it.
- Both hands. Hold it down.

34:16.576 --> 34:19.883
Evan, just stay with us.
Evan? Evan?

34:23.148 --> 34:24.584
Evan?

34:28.849 --> 34:32.026
- Evan. No! Evan...
- He's gone. He's gone.

34:33.593 --> 34:36.334
What...
This wasn't supposed to happen.

34:36.335 --> 34:37.857
This isn't... this isn't...

34:37.858 --> 34:40.077
Okay.

34:40.078 --> 34:42.557
I need... Myles.

34:42.558 --> 34:43.993
- No, no, no, no.
- No, no, no, no!

34:43.994 --> 34:45.604
- I have to get to Myles.
- Amy, Amy.

34:45.605 --> 34:47.562
- Look at me! He turned.
- No! Let me go.

34:47.563 --> 34:49.651
- No, the formula was working.
- Amy! Amy!

34:49.652 --> 34:51.566
It didn't!
It didn't last for him.

34:51.567 --> 34:53.612
- No!
- He turned. I'm sorry.

34:53.613 --> 34:55.396
We were too late with Myles.

34:55.397 --> 34:57.051
- I'm sorry.
- No.

34:59.053 --> 35:00.315
I'm sorry.

35:13.372 --> 35:15.373
I think we should just
stay here and wait for help.

35:15.374 --> 35:16.983
We're not staying here,
we can't stay here.

35:16.984 --> 35:18.332
We're not staying here.
There's no more time.

35:18.333 --> 35:20.029
No, if we leave here,
we are gonna die.

35:20.030 --> 35:22.162
If we stay, we die. Listen.

35:22.163 --> 35:25.339
No more guns, no more guards.
There's nothing left.

35:25.340 --> 35:27.428
Those things are coming for us.

35:27.429 --> 35:29.256
That door's not gonna stop them.

35:29.257 --> 35:31.476
Wes, think about
what you are saying.

35:31.477 --> 35:34.914
If we make it past those walls,
we're gonna face the moonlight.

35:34.915 --> 35:37.438
We got the formula. It works.

35:37.439 --> 35:39.658
We need more than the formula,
Wes. We need...

35:39.659 --> 35:40.964
Guns.

35:42.227 --> 35:45.534
- A plan.
- That is the plan.

35:48.058 --> 35:49.669
[insects trilling]

35:51.584 --> 35:52.672
[growling]

35:57.067 --> 35:59.548
- [howling]
- [breathing heavily]

36:20.656 --> 36:23.877
♪ ♪

36:32.842 --> 36:35.280
[grunts, gasps]

36:44.985 --> 36:46.681
[screams]

36:46.682 --> 36:49.294
[alarm sounding]

37:03.960 --> 37:05.570
[clanging]

37:05.571 --> 37:08.487
[clanging continues]

37:09.531 --> 37:11.838
[werewolf growling]

37:17.409 --> 37:19.148
[growling continues]

37:19.149 --> 37:21.500
[footsteps thudding]

37:30.596 --> 37:32.988
[howling]

37:32.989 --> 37:34.600
[bones crunching]

37:38.908 --> 37:40.388
[low growl]

37:54.097 --> 37:55.751
[growls]

37:56.970 --> 37:58.014
WESLEY: Fuck.

37:59.146 --> 38:02.367
- Get the weapons.
- Here, cover up.

38:23.953 --> 38:26.304
The formula will last
about an hour.

38:28.784 --> 38:30.524
Close your eyes.

38:30.525 --> 38:32.744
I'm gonna set my watch.
You set yours.

38:32.745 --> 38:34.007
If one of us turns...

38:35.051 --> 38:37.183
I'm not shooting you, Wes.

38:37.184 --> 38:39.707
If one of us turns,
we lose the other, yeah?

38:39.708 --> 38:41.927
- Yeah.
- Say it.

38:41.928 --> 38:43.103
Yes.

38:45.453 --> 38:47.802
When's the last time
you used one of these?

38:47.803 --> 38:51.415
Outside a paper target,
when you and I were in Malaysia.

38:51.416 --> 38:53.939
Well, let's pretend
they're paper targets

38:53.940 --> 38:56.029
that are gonna eat us.

38:59.902 --> 39:02.165
♪ ♪

39:04.907 --> 39:06.212
No.

39:06.213 --> 39:07.257
[whimpers]

39:09.564 --> 39:11.436
[growls]

39:12.175 --> 39:13.438
It's Myles.

39:14.308 --> 39:15.788
- [growls]
- Go.

39:22.229 --> 39:23.448
Don't slow down.

39:26.799 --> 39:28.017
I won't.

39:29.671 --> 39:31.369
[phone ringing]

39:32.979 --> 39:34.283
- LUCY: Wes.
- You guys okay?

39:34.284 --> 39:36.198
Yes, we're okay,
but there was gunfire.

39:36.199 --> 39:37.591
They got inside the houses.

39:37.592 --> 39:39.071
I know they're still out there.

39:39.072 --> 39:40.551
I know they are.
I just can't see them. I can't--

39:40.552 --> 39:41.987
What? What happened?

39:41.988 --> 39:43.771
I think they attacked Cody.
I saw them

39:43.772 --> 39:45.207
getting into his house.
And if they can get into his,

39:45.208 --> 39:47.166
- I just...
- Lucy, this is Dr. Chen.

39:47.167 --> 39:49.734
Just stay calm.
The noise will attract them.

39:49.735 --> 39:50.997
Okay. Okay.

39:52.607 --> 39:54.000
REAGAN:
Mrs. Marshall!

39:56.350 --> 39:57.872
- Luce?
- REAGAN: Mrs. Marshall,

39:57.873 --> 40:00.310
Mrs. Marshall, it's me!

40:09.842 --> 40:11.451
[whispers]:
There's someone at the gate.

40:11.452 --> 40:13.235
Don't answer it, okay?

40:13.236 --> 40:15.760
Mrs. Marshall, it's me, Reagan.

40:15.761 --> 40:17.849
[gasps]

40:17.850 --> 40:20.939
Oh, my God, it's-it's Reagan.
She's outside.

40:20.940 --> 40:22.897
I don't care who it is!
Don't answer it.

40:22.898 --> 40:25.073
- REAGAN: I need help!
- But...

40:25.074 --> 40:27.859
It killed my mom.
Please, Mrs. Marshall!

40:27.860 --> 40:32.124
[stammers] I can go get her.
I can cover up and go get her.

40:32.125 --> 40:33.734
Lucy, listen to me.

40:33.735 --> 40:35.736
It's Reagan, Wes.

40:35.737 --> 40:38.392
Don't answer it.
She could have turned. Lucy!

40:40.133 --> 40:42.351
- Hey, Reagan, hold on.
- Lucy!

40:42.352 --> 40:44.223
I'm gonna come get you,
all right? I'm gonna...

40:44.224 --> 40:45.311
[growling]

40:45.312 --> 40:46.965
No! No!

40:46.966 --> 40:48.923
- Don't answer the door.
- AMY: Wes.

40:48.924 --> 40:50.273
[Wesley grunts]

40:52.101 --> 40:53.363
Wes?

40:57.585 --> 40:59.152
[busy tone]

41:02.329 --> 41:03.678
[busy tone]

41:04.897 --> 41:06.464
[sobs]

41:07.856 --> 41:09.204
Oh, God.

41:09.205 --> 41:12.992
My home is a sacred ground. I...

41:14.646 --> 41:20.520
I will protect myself
and the ones I love.

41:20.521 --> 41:23.697
I am a survivor.
I am a strong...

41:23.698 --> 41:26.135
- [snarling]
- [screaming]

41:27.136 --> 41:28.442
Oh, my God!

41:31.401 --> 41:33.578
[growls]

41:34.753 --> 41:36.711
[roars]

41:38.800 --> 41:41.106
[continues sobbing]

41:41.107 --> 41:45.546
Fuck you, Sean. Fuck you,
you selfless hero prick! I...

41:49.942 --> 41:51.638
How could you?

41:51.639 --> 41:54.119
How could you leave us alone?
I... I...

41:54.120 --> 41:55.643
Oh, come here.

41:56.601 --> 41:58.341
[continues sobbing]

41:59.560 --> 42:02.823
- [sobs] I miss Daddy.
- I know you do.

42:02.824 --> 42:04.043
I know you do.

42:06.262 --> 42:07.525
I know, baby.

42:15.620 --> 42:17.360
[groaning]

42:26.587 --> 42:28.719
Go! Go!

42:28.720 --> 42:29.763
Move!

42:29.764 --> 42:32.027
[groans]

42:32.898 --> 42:34.160
[screams]

42:37.424 --> 42:40.295
- My phone.
- No, come on. Wes.

42:40.296 --> 42:42.429
- My phone.
- Get up! Get up!

42:43.169 --> 42:45.300
- Get up!
- [groans]

42:45.301 --> 42:47.956
Come on, Wes. Come on.

42:48.827 --> 42:50.872
[growling]

42:52.874 --> 42:54.572
[growls]

43:11.763 --> 43:14.503
Hey, I need you to stay
in your fort

43:14.504 --> 43:17.203
and keep your headphones on.
Can you do that for me?

43:18.160 --> 43:19.858
Go.

43:26.125 --> 43:28.170
♪ ♪

43:41.749 --> 43:43.621
There you are.

43:46.667 --> 43:49.061
[growls]

43:57.547 --> 43:59.506
This is for Reagan.

44:01.508 --> 44:03.641
[growls]

44:08.994 --> 44:10.952
[roars]

44:25.010 --> 44:26.880
Hey, listen.

44:26.881 --> 44:30.754
At this point,
all we are is prey.

44:30.755 --> 44:34.758
Wolves are predators, and they
hunt their prey on the run.

44:34.759 --> 44:36.674
What are you saying?
We shouldn't run?

44:39.285 --> 44:44.985
I'm saying, a wolf or two,
we can run, confuse them.

44:44.986 --> 44:48.337
But a big pack...
we got to stand our ground.

44:49.774 --> 44:51.600
In a wolf fight,

44:51.601 --> 44:55.388
you either dominate,
run, or die.

44:56.650 --> 44:59.130
No more options.

44:59.131 --> 45:00.827
In that case,
you stay as close to me

45:00.828 --> 45:02.395
as humanly possible. Yeah?

45:08.488 --> 45:10.490
- [growls]
- [car alarm blaring]

45:13.145 --> 45:14.537
[glass shattering]

45:17.758 --> 45:19.150
Fuck.

45:19.151 --> 45:21.283
[car alarm stops]

45:23.242 --> 45:24.938
I think we should backtrack
and cross over Fifth.

45:24.939 --> 45:29.551
No, it's too far.
We don't have that kind of time.

45:29.552 --> 45:32.946
Our only shot
is around these wolves.

45:32.947 --> 45:35.907
If we cross behind the
parked cars, they won't see us.

45:36.951 --> 45:38.299
Okay.

45:38.300 --> 45:41.041
And if we make it through,
what next?

45:41.042 --> 45:42.913
Let's cross that bridge
when we get to it.

45:42.914 --> 45:44.698
Stay close to me.

45:50.443 --> 45:51.705
[growling]

45:58.016 --> 45:59.887
[shattering continues]

46:16.208 --> 46:18.297
[growling]

46:29.221 --> 46:30.788
[objects crashing]

46:32.615 --> 46:36.358
[growling]

46:47.065 --> 46:50.328
[objects crashing]

46:50.329 --> 46:52.722
Where's the third one?
Where's the other one?

47:08.608 --> 47:09.957
[sniffs]

47:13.178 --> 47:14.961
[roars]

47:14.962 --> 47:16.398
[growls]

47:26.713 --> 47:28.846
[growling]

47:29.934 --> 47:32.327
[growling continues]

47:45.514 --> 47:47.952
- [werewolves growling]
- [glass shattering]

47:49.040 --> 47:52.130
- [thudding]
- [glass shattering]

47:58.484 --> 48:00.965
[footsteps receding]

48:03.358 --> 48:05.795
[growls]

48:07.275 --> 48:09.190
[sniffs]

48:18.156 --> 48:19.287
[roars]

48:20.680 --> 48:23.595
- [footsteps receding]
- [both sigh]

48:23.596 --> 48:26.251
[howling]

48:27.730 --> 48:29.471
[roars]

48:37.827 --> 48:39.873
♪ ♪

48:44.182 --> 48:45.705
- [howling]
- [gasps]

48:49.970 --> 48:51.450
[roars]

49:26.093 --> 49:28.877
- [watch beeping]
- WESLEY: Oh, shit.

49:28.878 --> 49:31.359
- The formula's gonna wear off.
- [growls]

49:33.187 --> 49:34.405
- Wes.
- WESLEY: Fuck.

49:34.406 --> 49:35.581
AMY:
I think we should run.

49:37.278 --> 49:40.846
- [growling]
- WESLEY: Go, go, go, go.

49:40.847 --> 49:42.717
- We have to get inside.
- AMY: How much time do we have?

49:42.718 --> 49:44.633
WESLEY:
There's no time.

49:48.942 --> 49:50.074
[roaring]

49:54.078 --> 49:55.557
[roaring]

49:59.300 --> 50:01.084
- There.
- Go.

50:01.085 --> 50:03.783
[alarm ringing]

50:05.959 --> 50:08.047
- AMY: The gates are closing.
- [roars]

50:08.048 --> 50:09.745
WESLEY:
Go, get in! Go!

50:15.012 --> 50:16.709
[snarling]

50:20.147 --> 50:21.148
BOY: Hey, guys.

50:22.889 --> 50:24.021
- Follow me.
- WESLEY: Hey!

50:36.816 --> 50:39.514
[people moaning]

50:42.474 --> 50:44.476
[banging on doors]

51:13.157 --> 51:16.289
- What is this place?
- It's a market.

51:16.290 --> 51:18.291
Its tunnels
run underneath there.

51:18.292 --> 51:20.425
We could use them
to bypass this shit.

51:23.819 --> 51:25.385
No!

51:25.386 --> 51:27.301
We don't want any trouble.

51:30.348 --> 51:32.044
I will shoot you in your face.

51:32.045 --> 51:36.570
We're scientists. There was
an accident at the lab.

51:36.571 --> 51:38.311
We're working on a cure.

51:38.312 --> 51:39.574
MAN [distorted]:
There is no cure.

51:45.450 --> 51:48.539
Your kind don't belong here.

51:48.540 --> 51:53.109
Give me a reason why I shouldn't
feed you to the wolves.

51:53.110 --> 51:54.632
We're just trying
to get to my family,

51:54.633 --> 51:56.590
make sure they're safe.
That's it.

51:56.591 --> 51:58.550
We just want to use the tunnels.

52:07.559 --> 52:10.300
I'll take you
to the tunnel entrance.

52:10.301 --> 52:14.043
Then... [chuckles]
you're on your own.

52:16.437 --> 52:18.178
[growling]

52:21.573 --> 52:23.705
[all growling]

52:30.886 --> 52:32.192
Oh, my God.

52:33.802 --> 52:37.763
[all snarling]

53:19.761 --> 53:21.807
♪ ♪

53:32.296 --> 53:34.298
♪ ♪

53:56.711 --> 53:58.017
[lock rattles]

54:00.454 --> 54:02.934
- Stand back.
- It's gonna be loud.

54:02.935 --> 54:04.371
Hold your ears.

54:06.852 --> 54:07.982
[thuds]

54:07.983 --> 54:10.029
[Amy breathing heavily]

54:15.904 --> 54:18.516
[low growl]

54:20.082 --> 54:22.301
- [snarls]
- Now!

54:22.302 --> 54:24.304
[both grunting]

54:25.610 --> 54:27.785
[werewolf snarling]

54:27.786 --> 54:29.483
[groans]

54:31.093 --> 54:32.269
[screams]

54:33.444 --> 54:34.923
- [roars]
- [Wesley groans]

54:38.275 --> 54:40.102
[screams]

54:53.768 --> 54:54.855
[screeches]

54:54.856 --> 54:56.901
[yells]

54:56.902 --> 54:58.643
[snarls]

55:00.209 --> 55:01.341
Die, you fuck.

55:02.124 --> 55:04.257
[yells]

55:10.872 --> 55:12.918
- [yells]
- [groans]

55:17.705 --> 55:20.186
Wes, come on, let's go. Get up.

55:36.942 --> 55:38.726
Stop!

55:42.948 --> 55:44.644
We need to reapply.

55:44.645 --> 55:46.646
[device beeping]

55:46.647 --> 55:48.997
- What does that mean?
- It's too hot.

55:51.217 --> 55:52.523
Bodega.

56:00.182 --> 56:01.270
Cover up.

56:10.105 --> 56:12.280
I don't care what you hear
or what you see,

56:12.281 --> 56:14.849
do not look up,
do not drop that tarp. Okay?

56:15.720 --> 56:16.721
My count.

56:19.245 --> 56:21.682
One, two, go!

56:29.516 --> 56:32.519
- [glass shattering]
- [alarm blaring]

56:33.868 --> 56:35.217
[both grunting]

56:36.305 --> 56:37.871
It's like a dinner bell.

56:37.872 --> 56:40.397
We need to shut it off.

56:45.402 --> 56:47.446
[alarm continues]

56:47.447 --> 56:49.406
- [grunts]
- [alarm crashes, stops]

57:07.032 --> 57:08.468
[growls]

57:37.497 --> 57:39.543
♪ ♪

57:47.855 --> 57:48.987
[exhales]

58:00.955 --> 58:02.348
[water running]

58:16.275 --> 58:17.581
[exhales]

58:18.495 --> 58:21.019
- [bag thuds]
- [grunts, sighs]

58:23.500 --> 58:25.719
- WESLEY: We good?
- It's close.

58:28.156 --> 58:30.071
[Wesley groans softly]

58:33.335 --> 58:35.250
You remember
when a full moon meant...

58:36.817 --> 58:39.167
...something cool and magical?

58:43.563 --> 58:46.523
God, we gotta find a way
back to that again.

58:48.220 --> 58:50.483
It's the only way
to go on with life.

58:53.225 --> 58:56.314
I don't even know
what that looks like anymore.

58:56.315 --> 58:58.622
"Go on with life." [scoffs]

59:00.667 --> 59:03.016
You know, I've been around
this planet five times over

59:03.017 --> 59:04.541
chasing pandemics?

59:08.414 --> 59:10.895
I never had time for a family.
I didn't want one.

59:13.071 --> 59:14.376
Give me a crisis...

59:15.813 --> 59:17.075
I can handle that.

59:22.167 --> 59:23.820
Now I have my brother's family,

59:23.821 --> 59:25.474
and I don't know
how to take care of 'em.

59:27.520 --> 59:29.304
You're giving them your best.

59:31.916 --> 59:33.873
That's the problem.

59:33.874 --> 59:36.355
I don't think
my best is good enough.

59:38.531 --> 59:40.314
[device beeping]

59:40.315 --> 59:42.274
AMY:
It's ready.

59:43.667 --> 59:45.319
All right.

59:45.320 --> 59:48.280
We just need to find
something to keep it cold.

59:50.325 --> 59:52.066
- I'll go check the back.
- Mm.

59:56.723 --> 59:58.986
[squelching]

01:00:24.708 --> 01:00:25.839
- [low snarl]
- Hey.

01:00:27.232 --> 01:00:30.670
Hey. How did you get in here?

01:00:31.758 --> 01:00:33.847
[low growl]

01:00:37.372 --> 01:00:38.896
Oh, fuck.

01:00:43.291 --> 01:00:44.641
Stop.

01:00:48.427 --> 01:00:49.471
Stop.

01:00:52.474 --> 01:00:53.780
I'm not gonna tell you again.

01:00:54.781 --> 01:00:56.391
Don't make me shoot you.

01:00:57.654 --> 01:00:58.785
- Stop!
- [growls]

01:01:00.526 --> 01:01:02.006
[groans]

01:01:04.443 --> 01:01:05.749
Jesus.

01:01:07.098 --> 01:01:08.185
I almost...

01:01:08.186 --> 01:01:10.622
[both breathing heavily]

01:01:10.623 --> 01:01:11.885
Just a kid.

01:01:13.321 --> 01:01:14.409
I know.

01:01:17.325 --> 01:01:19.458
Let's get out of here.

01:01:29.642 --> 01:01:31.078
[growls]

01:01:38.259 --> 01:01:40.044
[electricity crackling]

01:01:47.007 --> 01:01:48.705
Stay here, baby.

01:02:06.113 --> 01:02:08.811
My home is a sacred ground.

01:02:08.812 --> 01:02:12.902
I will protect myself and
the ones I love at all costs.

01:02:12.903 --> 01:02:15.034
I am a survivor.

01:02:15.035 --> 01:02:17.777
I am strong. I am capable.

01:02:18.778 --> 01:02:21.389
I bend, but I do not break.

01:02:22.042 --> 01:02:23.217
[shotgun cocks]

01:02:27.613 --> 01:02:31.660
Cody Walker, get the hell
off my property!

01:02:33.967 --> 01:02:36.403
- [shotgun cocks]
- You hear that?

01:02:36.404 --> 01:02:38.057
That's a 12-gauge shotgun,

01:02:38.058 --> 01:02:40.103
and I swear to God,
I'll blow your fucking head off.

01:02:40.104 --> 01:02:41.975
Yeah!

01:02:44.282 --> 01:02:45.413
Come here.

01:02:47.720 --> 01:02:49.940
♪ ♪

01:02:53.030 --> 01:02:55.162
[electricity crackling]

01:03:03.170 --> 01:03:04.998
I'm here.

01:03:15.617 --> 01:03:16.662
Oh, shit.

01:03:28.935 --> 01:03:30.067
[growls]

01:03:32.809 --> 01:03:34.722
LUCY:
Goddamn it!

01:03:34.723 --> 01:03:37.639
Come on. Come on. Stay with me.

01:03:39.380 --> 01:03:41.861
[clanging on door]

01:03:47.040 --> 01:03:49.172
- [clanging stops]
- [creaking]

01:03:49.173 --> 01:03:50.348
[Emma whimpers]

01:03:52.219 --> 01:03:53.699
[creaking]

01:03:56.833 --> 01:03:59.052
[thudding]

01:04:05.276 --> 01:04:07.452
Emma, get over here.

01:04:14.851 --> 01:04:15.852
Damn it.

01:04:17.375 --> 01:04:18.898
[roaring]

01:04:21.466 --> 01:04:22.684
Light this up
like we practiced, okay?

01:04:42.791 --> 01:04:44.967
Where are you?
I am not gonna warn you again.

01:04:44.968 --> 01:04:46.490
You leave now,
or I will shoot anyone

01:04:46.491 --> 01:04:48.840
that tries
to get inside my house.

01:04:48.841 --> 01:04:50.625
[footsteps thudding]

01:04:55.239 --> 01:04:58.024
- [thudding continues]
- [breathing heavily]

01:05:00.505 --> 01:05:04.029
- Fuck.
- [howling]

01:05:04.030 --> 01:05:05.727
[thudding continues]

01:05:07.164 --> 01:05:08.382
[thudding stops]

01:05:10.123 --> 01:05:11.819
[distant snarling]

01:05:11.820 --> 01:05:14.431
[screeching]

01:05:14.432 --> 01:05:17.217
Nails... it'll hold them.

01:05:18.566 --> 01:05:20.351
[distant gunfire]

01:05:22.919 --> 01:05:24.355
Hot, down.

01:05:28.315 --> 01:05:30.099
- MAN 1: Check your six!
- MAN 2: On it.

01:05:30.100 --> 01:05:31.535
Move.

01:05:31.536 --> 01:05:32.884
MAN 3:
Got one coming from northbound.

01:05:32.885 --> 01:05:34.190
MAN 4:
Shoot, motherfucker, shoot!

01:05:34.191 --> 01:05:36.062
MAN 5:
Good. Looks good.

01:05:42.068 --> 01:05:43.374
[indistinct shouting]

01:05:44.636 --> 01:05:45.898
MAN 6:
Move in!

01:05:48.379 --> 01:05:51.556
- MAN 7: On your left!
- MAN 8: He's running! Get him!

01:05:55.212 --> 01:05:56.647
Yeah!

01:05:56.648 --> 01:05:58.998
[machine powering up]

01:06:07.093 --> 01:06:08.573
MAN:
Move up! Move up!

01:06:11.054 --> 01:06:13.359
- Who are these guys?
- MAN: Get him now!

01:06:13.360 --> 01:06:15.623
I don't know, but they're gonna
get us the hell out of here.

01:06:18.583 --> 01:06:20.149
Forward!

01:06:20.150 --> 01:06:22.500
- [indistinct shouting]
- [roaring]

01:06:26.330 --> 01:06:28.853
MAN 1:
Ceasefire. Ceasefire.

01:06:28.854 --> 01:06:30.942
MAN 2:
Yeah, boys, they're gone.

01:06:30.943 --> 01:06:32.422
MAN 3:
Got 'em on the run.

01:06:32.423 --> 01:06:33.858
MAN 4:
Think we got 'em.

01:06:33.859 --> 01:06:34.946
Yeah, motherfucker.

01:06:34.947 --> 01:06:36.339
[laughs]

01:06:36.340 --> 01:06:37.601
Good shooting, men.

01:06:37.602 --> 01:06:38.906
- Hey!
- Stay right there!

01:06:38.907 --> 01:06:40.865
- MAN 1: Hey!
- MAN 2: Don't move.

01:06:40.866 --> 01:06:42.693
- No, no, no! We're friendlies.
- Don't move, motherfucker!

01:06:42.694 --> 01:06:44.434
BOTH:
Don't shoot.

01:06:44.435 --> 01:06:46.436
- Did you hear? Don't move!
- [overlapping shouting]

01:06:46.437 --> 01:06:47.785
- AMY: We're the CDC.
- We're friendlies.

01:06:47.786 --> 01:06:49.047
- We're with the CDC.
- Don't shoot!

01:06:49.048 --> 01:06:50.831
Stop talking.

01:06:50.832 --> 01:06:52.659
- Look, look. We're not turning.
- No, we're protected!

01:06:52.660 --> 01:06:54.400
- Look, look, look, look. We're
protected. -We're protected.

01:06:54.401 --> 01:06:57.012
- It blocks the light. It works.
- That's bullshit, man!

01:06:57.013 --> 01:06:58.448
- No, we're friendlies.
- Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.

01:06:58.449 --> 01:07:00.406
Don't shoot.

01:07:00.407 --> 01:07:01.581
Fuck!

01:07:01.582 --> 01:07:02.975
[indistinct shouting]

01:07:04.107 --> 01:07:05.325
Go forward.

01:07:13.333 --> 01:07:14.942
- [grunts]
- [growls]

01:07:14.943 --> 01:07:16.596
[both panting]

01:07:16.597 --> 01:07:18.773
[screaming]

01:07:20.166 --> 01:07:22.429
[gunfire continues]

01:07:36.574 --> 01:07:38.837
[growling]

01:07:47.237 --> 01:07:48.803
[gun clicks]

01:07:50.066 --> 01:07:51.110
[shotgun blast]

01:07:53.895 --> 01:07:55.071
[distant growling]

01:07:56.420 --> 01:07:57.942
- [howling]
- [shotgun blast]

01:07:57.943 --> 01:07:59.466
- [shotgun cocks]
- [growling]

01:08:00.815 --> 01:08:04.253
[shotgun blasting]

01:08:04.254 --> 01:08:05.732
- [screams]
- [shotgun blast]

01:08:05.733 --> 01:08:07.648
Mommy!

01:08:09.868 --> 01:08:10.956
[werewolf growls]

01:08:13.828 --> 01:08:15.743
- [shotgun clicks]
- Fuck.

01:08:16.396 --> 01:08:17.615
[grunts]

01:08:24.665 --> 01:08:25.884
Four left.

01:08:26.841 --> 01:08:28.974
[werewolves moaning]

01:08:29.844 --> 01:08:31.542
[werewolves screeching]

01:08:36.155 --> 01:08:38.201
[growls]

01:08:46.687 --> 01:08:48.080
[roars]

01:08:49.081 --> 01:08:50.603
They're forming a kill circle.

01:08:50.604 --> 01:08:52.257
If we stay here,
we're gonna die.

01:08:52.258 --> 01:08:54.607
- [screams]
- [crunching]

01:08:54.608 --> 01:08:57.480
We get to the Bronco.
It's our only shot.

01:08:57.481 --> 01:09:00.831
You get to that gun,
I'll be a distraction.

01:09:00.832 --> 01:09:02.833
- What?
- I have a theory.

01:09:02.834 --> 01:09:04.356
I'm going to test it.

01:09:04.357 --> 01:09:06.967
- No.
- You want to get to Lucy?

01:09:06.968 --> 01:09:08.361
Trust me.

01:09:09.841 --> 01:09:11.147
Don't die.

01:09:12.322 --> 01:09:14.105
Go.

01:09:14.106 --> 01:09:15.324
Hey!

01:09:15.325 --> 01:09:16.934
[snarls]

01:09:16.935 --> 01:09:18.415
Hey, you forgot one!

01:09:19.416 --> 01:09:20.852
Look at me.

01:09:25.509 --> 01:09:27.554
[growls]

01:09:33.256 --> 01:09:36.172
[sniffing]

01:09:38.783 --> 01:09:40.350
[whimpers]

01:09:49.881 --> 01:09:54.102
[screams]

01:09:55.539 --> 01:09:57.062
[grunts]

01:09:58.281 --> 01:10:02.676
[roars]

01:10:04.374 --> 01:10:05.418
WESLEY: Hey!

01:10:08.160 --> 01:10:09.335
Bite me.

01:10:29.399 --> 01:10:31.487
- [gunfire stops]
- [shell casings clatter]

01:10:31.488 --> 01:10:33.532
Amy! Now!

01:10:33.533 --> 01:10:35.840
♪ ♪

01:10:42.368 --> 01:10:43.630
Come on, come on, come on!

01:10:44.805 --> 01:10:46.719
